title: Super DIRT Week 2015: Friday's races officially postponed due to rain
text:
Syracuse, N.Y. — Friday's Super DIRT Week schedule of racing has been postponed until Saturday due to rain.
The officials made the announcement Friday afternoon.
We'll have an updated schedule for Saturday shortly.
With lingering light rain preventing track prep from being completed in timely fashion, officials have called off today's 'Cuse action.
— NAPA Super DIRT Week (@SuperDIRTWeek) October 9, 2015 Officials plan to run today's program - 358 & BB heats, Spts. qualifying - as part of Saturday's scheduled action ...
— NAPA Super DIRT Week (@SuperDIRTWeek) October 9, 2015 A full tentative schedule of events for Saturday's program will be posted shortly in live updates at http://t.co/MemGGVEaog ...
— NAPA Super DIRT Week (@SuperDIRTWeek) October 9, 2015
